<title>UK: Barclays sets 1.0 bln FRF perpetual bond.</title>
<headline>Barclays sets 1.0 bln FRF perpetual bond.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following subordinated step-up perpetual bond was announced by joint lead managers BZW and JP Morgan.</p>
<p> BORROWER   BARCLAYS PLC</p>
<p> AMT    1.0 BLN FRF   COUPON     6.50 PCT  MATURITY   *PERPETUAL</p>
<p> TYPE	 STRAIGHT  ISS PRICE  99.715    PAY DATE    07.JUL.97</p>
<p> FULL FEES  0.625     REOFFER    99.715    SPREAD	+65 BP</p>
<p> NOTES    *CALL OPTION ON 07.JUL.09, IF NOT CALLED, THE DEAL</p>
<p>BECOMES AN FRN PAYING 3MP+142BP OVER OATS, CALLABLE EVERY FIVE YEARS THEREAFTER</p>
<p> MOODY	AA3	 LISTING    PARIS     GOV LAW     ENGLISH</p>
<p> S&amp;P	  A+	  DENOMS (K) 10-100    SALE LIMITS US/UK</p>
<p> NEG PLG    NO	  CRS DEFLT  NO	  FORCE MAJ   IPMA (2)</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7658</p>
